        "caption": "Morpheus–OpenClaw Workshop\n\nAI and automation are changing how people work, build, and solve problems. But knowing where to start is often the hardest part.\n\nThis workshop gives you that starting point.\nThrough the OpenClaw Workshop, you’ll hear directly from the community leads at Morpheus (a decentralized AI ecosystem) and learn how it’s reshaping the way people access and use AI.\n\nInstead of relying on traditional paid models, Morpheus introduces concepts like staking tokens to access AI compute, opening up new possibilities for developers and builders. You’ll also see how this can be integrated with tools like OpenClaw to automate workflows and support real-world projects.\n\nNo prior experience with OpenClaw or decentralized AI? That’s completely fine. This session is designed to help you explore new skills and understand how these technologies can be applied in practical, everyday contexts.\n\n🎤 Speakers\n-Rene F Bernard\n-Eric Chan\n(Asia Community Leads @ Morpheus)\n\n📅 27 April 2026\n ⏰ 7:00 PM – 9:30 PM\n 📍 Agmo Space, FCM, MMU Cyberjaya\n\n✨ What you’ll gain:\n • Introduction to Morpheus & decentralized AI\n• Understanding token staking for AI compute\n• How OpenClaw integrates with AI workflows\n• Real use cases from community leaders\n• Networking with like-minded students\n\n🔗 Register: https://luma.com/ao3ija21",
